snippet.title: Severance — Season 2 Date Announcement | Apple TV+
snippet.description:
Like you never left. 

Severance season 2 premieres January 17, 2025 https://apple.co/_Severance 

In Severance, Mark Scout (Adam Scott) leads a team at Lumon Industries, whose employees have undergone a severance procedure, which surgically divides their memories between their work and personal lives. This daring experiment in “work-life balance” is called into question as Mark finds himself at the center of an unraveling mystery that will force him to confront the true nature of his work… and of himself.

In season two, Mark and his friends learn the dire consequences of trifling with the severance barrier, leading them further down a path of woe.

Season 2 reunites its ensemble cast of stars including Emmy Award nominee Adam Scott, Britt Lower, Tramell Tillman, Zach Cherry, Jen Tullock, Michael Chernus, Dichen Lachman, Emmy Award winner John Turturro, Academy Award winner Christopher Walken and Academy and Emmy Award winner Patricia Arquette, and welcomes new series regular Sarah Bock.

Severance is executive produced by Ben Stiller, who also directs five episodes this season in addition to directors Uta Bresiewitz, Sam Donovan and Jessica Lee Gagné. The series is written, created and executive produced by Dan Erickson. Severance season two is also executive produced by John Lesher, Jackie Cohn, Mark Friedman, Beau Willimon, Jordan Tappis, Sam Donovan, Caroline Baron, Richard Schwartz, Nicholas Weinstock. In addition to starring, Adam Scott and Patricia Arquette serve as executive producers. Fifth Season is the studio.

Subscribe to Apple TV’s YouTube channel: https://apple.co/AppleTVYouTube

snippet.title: Severance Theories #8 [Petey's Map + Theories]
snippet.description:

This time we look at the hand drawn map of the severed floor to see what clues we can uncover about Lumon and their plans AND, we talk about theories related to the map... because, of course we do. Also, I take a theory of a channel viewer and share it with the rest of the tinfoil gang.  

What is the coil of doom, team building?
What was Petey's plan and what exactly did he see before he escaped?

CREDIT: Redditor "Few_Addition9634" for the detailed closeup of the map.

snippet.title: Severance: What's Going on with Ms. Casey? Gemma Theories Season 1
snippet.description:
Severance: Ms. Casey Explained. Character study and theories on what Lumon is doing with this character. Please subscribe! 👉 http://bit.ly/PetePeppers

In the finale episode of Severance’s first season, Mark’s (Adam Scott) innie recognized Ms. Casey (Dichen Lachman) from the office in his wedding photo at his sister’s house. He knows her as the recently fired/retired Wellness Director on the Severed Floor at Lumon. Over the season we learned that she was a part-time innie, and that her total life was only 107 hours long. 
Mark’s main motivation for doing the severance procedure was the loss of his wife Gemma. Throughout the first season we see him struggle after her death. In the seventh episode we first saw that Ms. Casey looked exactly like her. This has been a big question since everyone around Mark appears to accept that she died in a car accident. 

In this video we look at the most popular theories for what’s up with the Ms. Casey situation. Did Mark’s wife fake her accident and voluntarily become a test subject for Lumon? Is this a robot or clone of Gemma? Is Lumon taking bodies from the hospital so they can experiment on them on the testing floor? 

Episode 9 ends on a big cliffhanger, but Apple TV+ has announced that Season 2 is coming. The season 1 finale provided a lot of answers, but most of the big mysteries are still intact. This video is a breakdown of what happened in the season 1 finale with a recap of the major plot points. We discuss what the ending means and discuss theories about Season 2. 

In the season 1 finale Mark's innie awakens in Devon's home and finds himself talking to Harmony Cobel. While excusing himself to find Devon, he calls Cobel by name, alerting her that the OTC protocol has been activated. Cobel calls Milchick and has him check the security office. Mark privately reveals to Devon that he is in innie form; Devon tells him of his wife Gemma's death, and learns that who she knows as "Mrs. Selvig" is Mark's boss. 

Irving wakes up in his apartment at the beginning of Episode 9, discovering his outie's paintings and military background, and finds a map and employee directory in the closet which he uses to locate Burt. Helly's innie wakes up at a Lumon gala where she learns that her outie is Helena Eagan - daughter of Lumon CEO Jame Eagan - who underwent severance to build public support for legalizing the procedure. 

Cobel races to the gala and attempts to stop Helly from exposing the abuses the innies suffer while severed in her public speech. Milchick reaches the security office and cuts his way through the makeshift restraints Dylan has placed on the door. Before the overtime contingency is stopped, Helly gets onstage and tells the crowd of the innies' subjugation and torment; Irving arrives at Burt's house only to find he is married to another man; Mark finds a photo from his outie's wedding to Gemma, thereby discovering that she is who he knows at work as Ms. Casey, and runs to tell his sister that his wife is still alive.



The Lexington Letter Severance Book (Free)

Apple Books: https://books.apple.com/us/book/severance/id1613220757
Non-Apple users: https://imgur.com/a/GOiKxEa

From director and executive producer Ben Stiller and creator Dan Erickson comes “Severance.” Mark Scout (Adam Scott) leads a team at Lumon Industries, whose employees have undergone a severance procedure, which surgically divides their memories between their work and personal lives. This daring experiment in “work-life balance” is called into question as Mark finds himself at the center of an unraveling mystery that will force him to confront the true nature of his work… and of himself.

The series is written and created by Dan Erickson. Mark Friedman, Chris Black, John Cameron and Andrew Colville are executive producers alongside Erickson. Ben Stiller, Nicky Weinstock and Jackie Cohn executive produce through Red Hour Productions, and both Patricia Arquette and Adam Scott serve as producers. Endeavor Content serves as the studio.

If you want to leave me a tip for my work 💰 https://paypal.me/petepeppersYT

An interview with Dan Erickson about the decision to keep things vague about the time period and tech
https://www.thewrap.com/severance-technology-setting-explained/

snippet.title: That Great SEVERANCE Ending! Season 1 Episode 9 Finale Recap & Breakdown
snippet.description:
Severance Season 1 Ending Explained. Severance episode 9 breakdown. Recap & review of "The We We Are" Season 1 finale. Please subscribe! 👉 http://bit.ly/PetePeppers

In the finale episode of Severance’s first season, Mark (Adam Scott), Helly (Britt Lower), and Irv (John Turturro) have their innies activated at home with Dylan’s (Zach Cherry) help. Harmony Cobel (Patricia Arquette) is with Mark at his sister’s party, and Helly is attending the Eagan Family Gala. We learn that her real name is Helena Eagan, and that she’s the current Lumon CEO Jame Eagan’s daughter. Milchick (Tramell Tillman) races against time to try to stop Dylan and disable the Overtime Contingency Protocol. 

Episode 9 ends on a big cliffhanger, but Apple TV+ has announced that Season 2 is coming. The season 1 finale provided a lot of answers, but most of the big mysteries are still intact. This video is a breakdown of what happened in the season 1 finale with a recap of the major plot points. We discuss what the ending means and discuss theories about Season 2.

The We We Are
The team discovers troubling revelations. Premiere Date: April 8, 2022
Written by: Dan Erickson
Directed by: Ben Stiller

Irving wakes up in his apartment at the beginning of Episode 9, discovering his outie's paintings and military background, and finds a map and employee directory in the closet which he uses to locate Burt. Helly's innie wakes up at a Lumon gala where she learns that her outie is Helena Eagan - daughter of Lumon CEO Jame Eagan - who underwent severance to build public support for legalizing the procedure. 

Cobel races to the gala and attempts to stop Helly from exposing the abuses the innies suffer while severed in her public speech. Milchick reaches the security office and cuts his way through the makeshift restraints Dylan has placed on the door. Before the overtime contingency is stopped, Helly gets onstage and tells the crowd of the innies' subjugation and torment; Irving arrives at Burt's house only to find he is married to another man; Mark finds a photo from his outie's wedding to Gemma, thereby discovering that she is who he knows at work as Ms. Casey, and runs to tell his sister that his wife is still alive.

The series is written and created by Dan Erickson. Mark Friedman, Chris Black, John Cameron and Andrew Colville are executive producers alongside Erickson. Ben Stiller, Nicky Weinstock and Jackie Cohn executive produce through Red Hour Productions, and both Patricia Arquette and Adam Scott serve as producers. Endeavor Content serves as the studio.

The Marvel Cinematic Universe has been going strong since 2008, but as of Phase Five, its story covers thousands of years. Need to catch up on the latest developments? Ah, let's just go through the whole thing.

#Marvel #MCU #Timelines

Vibranium comes to Earth | 6:19
Alien science and magic | 8:12
Life during wartime: the 1940s | 9:38
The Silver Age: the mid 20th century | 12:05
Recent history: the late 20th century | 14:19

snippet.title: The Downfall of The DCEU | A DC Documentary
snippet.description:
The DC Extended Universe. What was once seen as a potential rival to the massively successful Marvel Cinematic Universe, is now being abandoned after 16 movies and 1 show spanning a 10 year life time. Movies in general, have to earn 2 and a half times their budget to break even. The DCEU’s box office has been erratic to say the least, so throughout this documentary you will see some movies easily earn a profit and others failing to break even. This documentary highlights the 8 key moments of the DCEU. So join me today on this journey as we explore the downfall of the DCEU.

About this video essay:
We've all felt it: the movies have changed. But how so exactly, and why? And what can be done about it? In this extensive critique, I try to capture the decline of modern cinema in one unifying theory.

About this video essay:
We've all felt it: the movies have changed. But how so exactly, and why? And what can be done about it? In this extensive critique, I try to capture the decline of modern cinema in one unifying theory.

snippet.title: The Complete Philosophy of The Lord of the Rings
snippet.description:
Watch this video ad-free, and get access to exclusive content on Nebula: https://go.nebula.tv/lsoo

Help me make more videos!
Support this channel: https://www.patreon.com/LikeStoriesofOld 
Leave a One-Time Donation: https://www.paypal.me/TomvanderLinden

Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/LikeStoriesofOld 
Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/tom.vd.linden
Twitter: https://twitter.com/Tom_LSOO 

About this video essay:
An extensive analysis of the deeper meanings and philosophy of Tolkien’s The Lord of the Rings, and Peter Jackson’s adaptation, that examines Tolkien’s sanctification of pagan virtues, the role of heroism and moral victory in Middle-earth, the presence and purpose of higher forces, and the essential role of hope in Tolkien's mythology.
Originally published in 2 parts, this remastered edition features a completely new voice over track and audio mix, and corrected some minor mistakes.

Chapters:
0:00 Introduction
4:43 I. Sanctifying History
9:03 II. Military Victory vs. Moral Victory
11:52 III. At What Cost?
14:43 IV. Freedom and Evil
18:17 V. A Cosmic Conflict
21:51 VI. Responsibility and Salvation
25:38 VII. The Guiding Hand of Ilúvatar
32:18 VIII. A Mythology of Hope

Sources:
Matthew Dickerson – Following Gandalf: Epic Battles and Moral Victory in The Lord of the Rings: https://amzn.to/2P3jrFY 
Bradley Birzer – J.R.R. Tolkien’s Sanctifying Myth: Understanding Middle-earth: https://amzn.to/2LolSkq 
Peter Kreeft – The Philosophy of Tolkien: The Worldview Behind The Lord of the Rings: https://amzn.to/2wa5grO

snippet.title: The Complete Travels of Galadriel | Tolkien Explained
snippet.description:
Today, we follow Galadriel's life: her birth in Aman, exile with the rest of the Noldor, the first age in Beleriand, and her deeds in the second and third ages of Middle-earth.  From Galadriel's journey to Middle-earth, meeting her husband Celeborn, possessing Nenya - a Ring of Power, membership in the White Council, assisting the Fellowhip, and destroying Dol Guldur after the destruction of the One Ring - we will cover it all!  

Hit subscribe - and the bell - so you never miss a video from Nerd of the Rings!  NEW - you can know become a supporter of NOTR by hitting the JOIN button - you'll get exclusive emoji to use on YouTube, a username badge, and access to the supporter-only NOTR discord!

snippet.title: The Complete Travels of Legolas | Tolkien Explained
snippet.description:
Today, we track the entire life of Legolas: living in Mirkwood, his adventures as a member of the Fellowship, and his actions after the Return of the King.  Known for his fighting abilities and great senses, he comes to befriend the unlikeliest of companions - Gimli the Dwarf.  We will also cover his likely age as we look at his actions in the books.  Just as notable as his deeds during The Lord of the Rings are his actions after Sauron's fall, as he helps rebuild Minas Tirith and ultimately sails west with his best friend.

Hit subscribe - and the bell - so you never miss a video from Nerd of the Rings!

snippet.title: The Complete Travels of Gimli | Tolkien Explained
snippet.description:
We tell the life story of Gilmi, son of Glóin. One of the greatest dwarves of the Third Age, Gimli is known for his fighting, his ferocity, and his friendships.  We cover his beginnings in the Blue Mountains, west of The Shire, to his time in Erebor, his journeys as a member of the Fellowship of the Ring, and his time after The Lord of the Rings as Lord of the Glittering Caves.

snippet.title: The Complete Travels of Saruman | Tolkien Explained
snippet.description:
Covering the complete tale of Saruman the White, from his origins and early travels in the East, taking control of Isengard, and creating his own ring, all the way through to his eventual death in The Shire.  We will track all of Saruman's travels and deeds as he turns from a great wizard to an ally of Sauron to a traitor to both the Dark Lord and the White Council.

snippet.title: The Life of Elrond Half-elven | Tolkien Explained
snippet.description:
Elrond is one of the most important characters throughout The Lord of the Rings, The Hobbit, and the Silmarillion. His life would be one full of significance, but also separation from those he loved. Through hardship and war, he would rise to become one of the wisest and most powerful rulers in Middle-earth.

snippet.title: 3 Years of Brutality & Brotherhood: A Chronology of the Clone Wars' Ground Battles
snippet.description:
Embark on an epic journey through the most important battles of the Clone Wars in this comprehensive 4-hour video. Witness the galaxy-shaking conflicts that defined the era, as we explore each battle in chronological order. From the pivotal Battle of Geonosis to the climactic Siege of the Jedi Temple, relive the heroic struggles of the Jedi, the relentless onslaught of the Separatists, and the courage of the Clone Army. Immerse yourself in the rich history of the Star Wars universe and experience the unforgettable moments that shaped the fate of a galaxy far, far away.

snippet.title: The Most Brutal Period of the Clone Wars & It's Not Even Close - A Deep Look At the Outer-Rim Sieges
snippet.description:
Thanks to the machinations of Darth Sidious, the Clone Wars were a stalemate for most of their duration. For years, the Republic and the CIS fought a back-and-forth war, each capturing and losing territory in turn. Until the Battle of Coruscant, most of the galaxy was under the impression that there was no end to the war in sight. But starting in late 20 BBY, the truth was that the Republic was winning. Slowly but surely, the Republic had begun to centralize and rally its industrial might, and by the start of 19 BBY, it was pushing Separatist forces back on every front, bringing the fight to the Rimward strongholds of the Confederacy. These grueling final months of the Clone Wars were known as the Outer Rim Sieges, and in this long-form video we’ll be telling the full story of this bloody chapter of the war.

snippet.title: What if Iron Man BUILT Darth Vader’s Suit?
snippet.description:
What if Iron Man BUILT Darth Vader’s Suit? Let’s explore the depths of this scenario in the video.

Tony Stark shudders as a low humming device shrieks into his ear, leaving his body frozen in place. Standing above him is his former mentor, Obadiah Stane. He slowly pulls out the arc reactor from his chest and holds it up for him to see.

Obadiah: Oh, it's beautiful. Tony, this is your Ninth Symphony. What a masterpiece. Look at that. This is your legacy. A new generation of weapons with this at its heart. Weapons that will help steer the world back on course, put the balance of power in our hands. The right hands. I wish you could've seen my prototype. 

He begins to place the arc reactor into a briefcase and prepares to leave.

Obadiah: I already have a buyer. Someone very interested in the armor you’ve made.

Suddenly, Obadiah’s watch begins to beep as a figure begins to call him. It’s a figure cloaked in black and hidden by a dark mask.

Vader: Not just the armor. Is this the man who built the armor?

Obadiah: Yes, sir. The one and only Tony Stark.

Vader stares into the paralyzed man’s eyes, sensing great power in him even without the Force.

Vader: I shall have him too.

Obadiah: Surprised. My lord, that wasn’t part of our agreement.

Vader: The armor you’ve created is crude compared to what he can make. This man is more valuable than any piece of tech you can give me. Do not worry, though; he shall not pose a threat to your takeover. I intend to take him far away from your world.

Obadiah: I’ve tried taking him far away, and he still came back. Where will you bring him?

Vader: Into my home, in a galaxy far, far away.

Obadiah looks at the man in surprise, wondering if he’s joking or not. But Vader appears completely serious. He quickly agrees, placing the arc reactor back into Tony’s chest but keeping him paralyzed as he prepares him for transport.

A few minutes later, an imperial shuttle lands outside the Stark mansion and carries Tony away to Mustafar. On the way back, Vader keeps Tony imprisoned in a ray shield as he looks over the information that Obadiah provided him about Tony. He’s surprised and impressed to see what man has accomplished with the limited technologies of this planet. In some ways, he reminds Vader of himself when he was still Anakin—a genius inventor who also tried to change the world from injustice.

For that reason, Vader allows Tony to keep his memories, but his surgical droid places an inhibitor chip in his brain. This chip is programmed by Vader himself, commanding Tony to be loyal to him and placing special command codes when he activates it.

After weeks of travel, they arrive at Vader’s castle on Mustafar. He takes Tony down to the lab, which is lined with state-of-the-art tools and more equipment than any Stark lab.

Even imprisoned, Tony could not help but be impressed.

Vader: I was told by your mentor that you built the most powerful suit of armor your world has ever known in, as he puts it, ‘a cave with a box of scraps.’ But as impressive as that armor is, it is rather primitive. I think with my tools you shall make something far greater.

Tony: I made that suit to save myself and to protect people from tyrants. What makes you think that I’m just going to make you one?

Vader: Because I also know the sting of a master’s betrayal. The difference is my master isn’t some money-grubbing businessman; he’s an emperor who rules the greatest empire your world has known.

Tony: And I’m supposed to believe you’re gonna bring peace? Yeah, the black leather and red glowing sword aren’t convincing me.

Vader: Then perhaps you can bring that peace yourself.

Vader snaps his fingers, and two droids come in, carrying one of the Iron Man suits in a crate.

Vader: Obadiah’s plans are nothing to me. Here is my deal: help me create my armor, and I shall allow you to return to Earth and overthrow your master.

Tony: And why should I believe that?

Vader: Because, as I said, you are not the only one who felt the betrayal of a master.

For the first time since arriving, Tony feels the sincerity of those words. Slowly, he agrees to help him. The two immediately get to work on the armor.

First, he studies Vader’s existing suit and looks for ways to upgrade it. The Dark Lord takes an active role in these upgrades, using his knowledge of engineering to help in the designs.

The two find weak points and begin correcting them, such as improving the comfort and sensors of the armor, then modifying the needles to allow Vader to control the amount of pain he feels. Lastly, Tony replaces the material with beskar.

After that, he adds additional modifications, placing rocket boosters and repulsor lasers that allow Vader to fight without his lightsaber. These are also enhancements that will increase Vader’s strength, speed, and endurance.

Meanwhile, Tony also begins working on his armor, making upgrades to it with the new weapons this galaxy has to offer. Vader is more than happy

A few minutes later, an imperial shuttle lands outside the Stark mansion and carries Tony away to Mustafar. On the way back, Vader keeps Tony imprisoned in a ray shield as he looks over the information that Obadiah provided him about Tony. He’s surprised and impressed to see what man has accomplished with the limited technologies of this planet. In some ways, he reminds Vader of himself when he was still Anakin—a genius inventor who also tried to change the world from injustice.

For that reason, Vader allows Tony to keep his memories, but his surgical droid places an inhibitor chip in his brain. This chip is programmed by Vader himself, commanding Tony to be loyal to him and placing special command codes when he activates it.

After weeks of travel, they arrive at Vader’s castle on Mustafar. He takes Tony down to the lab, which is lined with state-of-the-art tools and more equipment than any Stark lab.

Even imprisoned, Tony could not help but be impressed.

Vader: I was told by your mentor that you built the most powerful suit of armor your world has ever known in, as he puts it, ‘a cave with a box of scraps.’ But as impressive as that armor is, it is rather primitive. I think with my tools you shall make something far greater.

Tony: I made that suit to save myself and to protect people from tyrants. What makes you think that I’m just going to make you one?

Vader: Because I also know the sting of a master’s betrayal. The difference is my master isn’t some money-grubbing businessman; he’s an emperor who rules the greatest empire your world has known.

Tony: And I’m supposed to believe you’re gonna bring peace? Yeah, the black leather and red glowing sword aren’t convincing me.

Vader: Then perhaps you can bring that peace yourself.

Vader snaps his fingers, and two droids come in, carrying one of the Iron Man suits in a crate.

Vader: Obadiah’s plans are nothing to me. Here is my deal: help me create my armor, and I shall allow you to return to Earth and overthrow your master.

Tony: And why should I believe that?

Vader: Because, as I said, you are not the only one who felt the betrayal of a master.

For the first time since arriving, Tony feels the sincerity of those words. Slowly, he agrees to help him. The two immediately get to work on the armor.

First, he studies Vader’s existing suit and looks for ways to upgrade it. The Dark Lord takes an active role in these upgrades, using his knowledge of engineering to help in the designs.

The two find weak points and begin correcting them, such as improving the comfort and sensors of the armor, then modifying the needles to allow Vader to control the amount of pain he feels. Lastly, Tony replaces the material with beskar.

After that, he adds additional modifications, placing rocket boosters and repulsor lasers that allow Vader to fight without his lightsaber. These are also enhancements that will increase Vader’s strength, speed, and endurance.

Meanwhile, Tony also begins working on his armor, making upgrades to it with the new weapons this galaxy has to offer. Vader is more than happy

snippet.title: What if Count Dooku & Mace Windu BOTH Turned to the Dark Side?
snippet.description:
What if Count Dooku and Mace Windu BOTH Turned to the Dark Side? Let’s explore the depths of this scenario in the video.

The Jedi Council is not pleased as Dooku and Mace Windu stand before them. Both Jedi recently finished a mission to Raxulon to investigate the death of Jedi Master Katri. While a success, Dooku greatly overstepped his authority and the council is concerned about this behavior.

Ki-Adi Mundi: We understand the quest for justice is long and difficult, but there are limits one must follow when pursuing it.

Dooku: Yes, yes. I am well aware of the protocol that must be followed, as you have informed me many times.

Yoda: And ignored them, you have. Many times.

Dooku: With all due respect, masters. There was little time to report everything. The longer we waited, the more opportunities the killers would have to cover up their evidence.

Yoda: And what of threatening the senator, Master Dooku?

Mace: Master Dooku acted rashly, I understand. But the blame is not only his.

Yoda: On that, we agree. This behavior, we expected from him. Which is why sent you, we did.

Mace: Are you saying I am to blame for this situation?

Tera Sinube: What we are saying is that there are expectations of how Jedi Masters must behave and that we had expected more from both of you.

Yoda: Dismissed you two are, discuss this situation, the council must.

Both Jedi march away  in a huff, neither one saying a word to the other as they head  to their quarters to cool off. Mace attempts to meditate, reflect, and understand the Council’s decision. But despite his best efforts, he finds no wisdom, only frustration.

He’s a Jedi Master, and so is Dooku. Why is it his job to control him? Suddenly, a voice echoes through his head.

Palpatine: A frustrating thing, isn’t it? When bureaucracy and protocol take precedence.

Mace opens his eyes and a hooded figure stands before him. He leaps to his feet and draws his lightsaber.

Mace: Who are you? State your business!

Palpatine: Chuckles. Peace, my friend. I am simply here to talk.

Mace: I am in no mood to talk with anyone, especially intruders like you.

Palpatine: Oh? You are barbaric for one who prides himself in fighting for civilization.

Mace: Unless you have information of any relevance, then you have no business wasting my time.

Palpatine: Oh, I do, though it may be information you already know. Larik is far from the only corrupt senator out there. Look into the Senate, and you shall find hundreds more just like him. All stealing from their worlds, selling their people, and betraying the Republic they fought for.

Mace: Is that supposed to entice me? You say what every vagabond and street urchin can tell me.

Palpatine: And yet the Jedi Council turns a blind eye to it. The Jedi have failed you, Mace. They failed Dooku as well. They are blind to their hypocrisy and weakness. But there are ways to change this galaxy for the better for those willing to reach out and take it.

Before Mace can respond, the vision begins to fade, and he finds himself alone in his quarters. Little does he know, Dooku has received similar visions.

To their dismay, the council decides that both Jedi require a break from active duty to cool off and hopefully teach them patience. They will work in the library and train the younglings.

Mace uses this opportunity to try and purge these negative emotions by throwing himself into his work. As he spars with the other masters or trains with the padawans, he allows those negative feelings to flow through him.

It seems to help Mace’s mood as he begins to feel better and doesn’t receive any more visions for the next few weeks. However, Dooku spends his time in the library. When he’s not sorting through the archives, Palpatine discreetly begins sending classified documents that show the Senate’s corruption.

Dooku verifies the claims Palpatine sends him int he archives and with his contacts. He sees entire worlds being sold to corporations, cities left to ruin or at the mercy of pirates, and political murder on an unprecedented scale. 

He brings many of these issues to the Jedi, begging them to investigate, but they either don’t believe him or the bureaucracy and protocol prevent them from launching any meaningful investigation.

Dooku grows increasingly frustrated with the Jedi's inability to do anything. He even warns them that this might be a sign of the coming dark side. But rather than act, they decide to once again wait and see.

Mace hears of this and pulls Dooku aside one day.

Mace: Whatever may come, know that despite our differences I am ready to stand with you.

Dooku: As am I, my friend. But alas, we are at the mercy of the Jedi Council.

Unfortunately, the first encounter with the Sith is with neither Mace nor Dooku, but with the latter's apprentice, Qui-Gon who is slain by Darth Maul.

Shortly after, Dooku mysteriously vanishes from the Order. No one, not even Mace, knows what happened to him. No one takes the blow harder than

snippet.title: What if Droids SAVED the Jedi During Order 66?
snippet.description:
What If The Droids Saved The Jedi During Order 66? Let’s explore the depths of this scenario in the video.

After the Battle of Onderon, Republic strategists, including the Jedi, discuss the latest developments. Although it was a Republic victory, they observed troubling changes in the droids' behavior.

The droids were better disciplined and employed smarter tactics. There were rumors that the Separatists were deploying a new generation of super tactical droids that were better commanders than the standard droid commanders.

The Battle of Onderon confirmed these rumors, as both Saw Gerrera and the royal military reported the presence of these droids.

Captain Rex: This poses a problem for our strategists. The droids use algorithms to predict our moves and develop counter-maneuvers for our tactics. It's why the tricks we use become less effective over time. If they have new commanders, our strategies can become outdated even faster."

Anakin: "Well, I guess we just have to be smarter than them."

Obi-Wan: "Unfortunately, things are not that simple. It won’t matter how smart we are if these droids can predict our moves. What we need is some intelligence on these droid models."

Cody: "I’m glad you mentioned that, General. I propose a standing order for Republic troops to capture an intact super tactical droid for analysis. That way, we can let the boys figure out how they work."

The other officers agreed to this proposal and got their opportunity during the Battle of Ringo Vinda. In the final stages of the campaign, clone trooper Tup’s inhibitor chip malfunctioned, causing him to activate Order 66 prematurely. The droid commander of this operation, Kraken, noticed this and was ordered by Admiral Trench to capture Tup for examination. However, his transport was intercepted by Anakin, Fives, and Rex. 

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vGh6J2hywgg 3:30-3:46

The clones storm the shuttle, cutting down the droid guards. Kraken leaps forward and scores a few blows before Anakin slices off his arms. As the droid stumbles back, he holds his lightsaber against him.

Anakin: Whats going on? What do you know about this clone?

Kraken: I am programmed to resist intimidation.

Although Anakin wants to destroy him, he knows there is too much data in that droid to risk losing. Instead, he takes a droid popper from Fives and temporarily disables him.

They take Kraken back to Coruscant to begin going through his databanks. This proves to be more difficult than they think, as many of the droid's logs are protected, stifling the efforts of the researchers.

One person who offers to help is Anakin. Using his years of experience building and modifying droids, he helps the research team crack the codes keeping them out of the databanks.

They immediately begin poring over the files and recordings of the droid. One of the most recent ones that got their attention was a conversation between Dooku and Trench regarding Tup. As Anakin and the research team listen to it, they notice the change in Dooku's demeanor after he hears Trench’s report. They note how hurriedly he ends the transmission just as Tup is kidnapped shortly after.

Kraken: "What are you doing to me?"

Anakin: "Getting answers, droid. Now try not to cause too much of a fuss. We don’t want to cause a malfunction."

Kraken: "You mean like your soldier?"

Anakin: "Careful, droid. That's a living thing you’re talking about."

Kraken: "One who had something malfunctioning in his brain. I saw the situation, Jedi. Look how that clone moved and started acting. He did not simply attack you because he wanted to; he could not help himself. How can that happen unless something in his head was malfunctioning or someone made him do it?"

Anakin can’t think of a rebuttal. Although he hates to admit it, the droid raises a good point. Tup’s behavior was odd. Instead, he turns his attention back to gathering more information on the super tactical droid.

He learns that these command droids transmit signals to the other droids, relaying instructions, which is how they can coordinate battles. With this information, Anakin and the other Jedi begin researching how to replicate these commands to try and take control of at least a portion of the droids.

Despite this victory, Anakin cannot let himself rest easy as Kraken’s words continue to ring in his head. A seed of doubt grows in his mind, especially as he hears Fives mentioning some inhibitor chip.

However, the ARC trooper dies before he reveals more, leaving Anakin with no leads. Palpatine himself visits Anakin after the clone's funeral and assures Anakin that he is not to blame for what happened and that Fives’ death was due to battlefield stress and substance abuse.

snippet.title: Superman vs Hulk - The Fight (Part 4)
snippet.description:
✧ FOR THOSE WHO WOULD LIKE TO LEAVE A TIP FOR THE ARTIST AND HELP WITH THE PRODUCTION OF THESE VIDEOS, SEE LINKS BELOW AND THANKS IN ADVANCE ✧
PATREON ➤  https://www.patreon.com/user?u=4171003
PAYPAL ➤  paypal.me/mikehabjan
⚊⚊⚊⚊⚊⚊⚊⚊⚊⚊⚊⚊⚊⚊⚊⚊⚊⚊⚊⚊⚊⚊⚊⚊⚊⚊⚊⚊⚊⚊⚊⚊⚊

I have no idea about when part 5 will be done... probably within the next 30 years though. No promises. It's difficult work.
❤ THANKS FOR WATCHING AND HAVE A NICE DAY ❤

⊗ PLEASE DO NOT REUPLOAD ⊗ Reuploading my videos to your channel drives traffic away from my channel and makes it more difficult to continue this project!  This was four years to make and I rely on YouTube earnings to make these in the first place.  If you would like to share my work,  use the video URL to link back to here. If you want to do reaction video with the animation small in the corner that's fine.


✧ ABOUT THE PROJECT ✧
⚊⚊⚊⚊⚊⚊⚊⚊⚊⚊⚊⚊⚊⚊⚊⚊⚊⚊⚊⚊⚊⚊⚊⚊⚊⚊⚊⚊⚊⚊⚊⚊⚊

Here is the continuation of Part 3 of Superman vs Hulk. When last we left our heroes Superman was mightily flying Hulk up into the sky. I hear all the time, Superman would just fly Hulk into space and be done with it. I always thought Hulk would put up a bit of a fight and maybe not just let Superman fly him into space. Anyway the fight in the sky I thought would be cool after a lot of ground fighting. So this is my interpretation of what might happen if they were to do battle in the sky.

I use the 80's film and television versions of these characters as that as what I grew up watching and inspired this in the first place. Christopher Reeve's likeness is used as in the previous version with slight model enhancements from the last one. I chose to give Hulk a closer resemblance to Lou Ferrigno, in face and body proportion but an eight foot tall, even more jacked version, minus the goofy wig.  I use their likeness with all respect and hope it does their portrayals justice.

As stated above this was four years in the making. I usually work about 50 hours a week, pretty much whenever I'm home and render day and night on three work computers. There were times I was not interested in working on it and from time to time I take little breaks or go on vacation. Also had taken a studio job doing visual effects for about 8 months for a break and also earn some cash and learn new skills. So if I hadn't done any of that it may have been done almost a year earlier but that's the way it goes. I need a break from it. At a certain point I was really tired of working on it and not really liking it at all. I will share those videos soon so watch for them. Each shot went through many revisions and a lot of stuff was changed or taken out over the years. Took a while to find the right beats to hit. I think it turned out alright though not perfect or studio quality. It was a lot more difficult to stage a sky battle than I thought it would be, a lot more than a ground fight, so I kind of look forward to continuing it on the ground.

Terragen was used for making the environment and Maya for the characters. Nuke for compositing and Vegas for editing.

Francois Gratecap again did the excellent music work and a first pass at the sound design but that was when the video was not complete so I took over the sound design for a lot of it so forgive the less than perfect sound quality.

Christopher Reeve's likeness is used as in the previous version with slight model enhancements from the last one. I chose to give Hulk a closer resemblance to Lou Ferrigno, in face and body proportion but an eight foot tall, even more jacked version, minus the goofy wig.  I use their likeness with all respect and hope it does their portrayals justice.

As stated above this was four years in the making. I usually work about 50 hours a week, pretty much whenever I'm home and render day and night on three work computers. There were times I was not interested in working on it and from time to time I take little breaks or go on vacation. Also had taken a studio job doing visual effects for about 8 months for a break and also earn some cash and learn new skills. So if I hadn't done any of that it may have been done almost a year earlier but that's the way it goes. I need a break from it. At a certain point I was really tired of working on it and not really liking it at all. I will share those videos soon so watch for them. Each shot went through many revisions and a lot of stuff was changed or taken out over the years. Took a while to find the right beats to hit. I think it turned out alright though not perfect or studio quality. It was a lot more difficult to stage a sky battle than I thought it would be, a lot more than a ground fight, so I kind of look forward to continuing it on the ground.

Terragen was used for making the environment and Maya for the characters. Nuke for compositing and Vegas for editing.

Francois Gratecap again did the excellent music work and a first pass at the sound design but that was when the video was not complete so I took over the sound design for a lot of it so forgive the less than perfect sound quality.

snippet.title: Most Brutal 1v1 Hand-to-Hand Fight Scenes
snippet.description:
0:00 Universal Solider: Regeneration
2:06 Killzone
4:09 The Punisher - Season 2
6:41 The Man From Nowhere
8:23 Boyka: Undisputed
9:50 The Raid 2

If you have been subbed to my channel for a long time (a long time being at least 6 months in this case) then you might get a little déjà vu when watching this video. Thats because this is my first re-uploaded compilation, since it was blocked a while ago when it was at around 150k views. So I decided to remake it with better quality clips and, obviously, without the clip that got it blocked in the first place. Even though this video is technically unblocked, it still ended up being blocked on mobile which means a lot of my subs wont be able to see this one, unfortunately. Three of the clips i featured are blocked on mobile which means to get around it, Id basically need to make a whole new video which I dont have time for. Sorry about that y'all.
 
Anyways, this compilation focuses on brutal 1v1 fights where in each fight, their lives are on the line. These fights are all pretty intense, whether they are using their fists or knives. But like always, I tried to vary it up a bit so no two fights are too similar. Let me know what your favorite fight is, mine is definitely the knife fight from the Man from Nowhere; the sound design is top notch, plus the choreography and cinematography is just badass.

Just a heads up to my subs, I got classes starting in a few days so while Im going to try to stick to my one video a week schedule, It might start leaning towards a video every week and a half a little later on in the semester. So if I dont get a video out within a week, just know I haven't forgotten about y'all ;) a video is definitely on its way.

Love you guys, stay safe and be good people

snippet.title: Most Creative Hand-to-Hand Fight Scenes Pt.2
snippet.description:
0:00 The King's Man
3:50 Tenet
7:05 John Wick: Chapter 3 - Parabellum
9:20 Inception
11:51 Upgrade
13:54 Reacher - Season 1

Alright y'all I got a banger for you guys today. I decided to compile a 2nd part to my creative hand to hand fight scenes. I even got some clips from newer shows/movies so I hope this doesn't end up getting blocked, I got my fingers crossed. But anyway, This video features fights that I believe have a creative premise, choreography, and/or have creative endings/kills. I usually like to finish off my videos with my favorite clip, but this one I decided to start with my favorite, which was the silent fight from The King's Man. You cant get any more more badass and creative then 2 opposing squads running into each other at midnight in the middle of a battlefield and deciding to throw down with knives and shit in order to not start a full blown battle. Plus, I managed to get a clip from the new show Reacher which was a really fun show, I recommend it to anyone who likes my videos. I could watch Thad Castle kick ass all day. Anyway, I hope you all enjoy, let me know what other fights I may have missed and as always;

Love you guys, stay safe and be good people

5:23 Tenet

Hey y’all! Today I put together part 8 to my badass movie moments series. I got a little of everything, including some newer movies, so I’m sure you will find at least one movie you’d like to check out. I tried to add a scene from the movie Brawl in Cell Block 99 but got blocked since they are super uptight about that movie, so Id suggest just watching it in its entirety. If you like my videos, I guarantee you'll like it, I have just never been able to share it with you all through my videos. Anyways, I did get to end this video with one of my favorite fight scenes of recent memory so be sure to stick around for that. So I hope you all enjoy the latest installment to my favorite series, the most badass scenes on YouTube! 

Happy holidays to all, and I hope this year was good to everybody! Sorry I’ve been so inactive with my videos this year,  I never forgot about you all, I've just been caught up with my internship. I had a really good 2021 and I hope you all did too. Speaking of that, thank you all so much for 100k subscribers, It was such an awesome milestone to hit! Even though I was inactive, my channel was still being shown love and I really appreciate that. I dont know how often I will be posting in the future, but I will try to make it happen more often going in to the new year. So thank you again guys, its been amazing creating these videos for you all and I can not wait to check out even more awesome scenes with you guys in 2022.

Love you guys, stay safe and be good people.

snippet.title: Most Savage Movie Moments Pt.2
snippet.description:
0:00 Kick‐Ass
0:54 True Detective ‐ Season 2
3:26 The Boys ‐ Season 2
6:40 Drive
9:32 The Punisher ‐ Season 1
13:24 The Irishman
14:58 Inglorious Basterds

Alright, I'm back! Today I got the 2nd part to my savage movie moments series. These are some of my favorite clips where our hero goes a little overboard (sometimes understandably, and sometimes not). Nevertheless, these are some brutal clips. I think the opening scene sets the tone very well for the rest of the video, so if you cant stomach that, maybe this one isn't for you. I attempted to add some newer movies into the mix like Tax Collector, but YouTube wasn't having it, so I stuck to the movies that I know and love like Inglorious Basterds and shows like The Boys, both of which are full of savage moments. Either way, I hope you enjoy!

Sorry for the long break in uploads, I was feeling a little uninspired the last few months and I was running out of clips. The way I make these videos is I build of lists of clips over time, and filter out ones that dont match or dont fit with the others. But recently I haven't been watching as many new movies, which means I haven't been building as many lists. I've just been focusing more on my studies, working out and spending time with my friends. I actually recently got invited to do a Co‐op internship at a company doing I.T.! I'm really excited about that. But recently I've been feeling inspired again so I decided to put together for a video for my awesome subscribers. I'm very fortunate to see that my channel has actually grown in my absence, so I want to welcome my new subscribers! Though I cant promise that ill be posting weekly like I used to, I am going to make more of an effort to post some more videos in the near future. I always try to put out videos that are high quality and that I myself enjoy, which sometimes takes time, as well as trial and error. But thank you all so much for sticking around and I hope you all are having a good 2021 so far.

and as always; I love you guys, stay safe and be good people.

snippet.title: Galadriel’s Entire Backstory Explained
snippet.description:
Peter Jackson’s Lord of the Rings trilogy is one of the greatest fantasy trilogies of all time. It brought some of J.R.R. Tolkien's most beloved characters to life, like Gandalf, Aragorn, and Legolas, but fans of the books would have loved to see more of the powerful elf Galadriel.

Galadriel was played to a tee by the talented Cate Blanchett, and even though her appearances in the trilogy proved pivotal, they paled in comparison to her memorable appearances in Tolkien's books.

For those of you who want to take a deep dive into the history of one of the mightiest elves in Middle-earth, here is Galadriel’s entire backstory.

#LordOfTheRings #Books #Movies

snippet.title: The Hobbit illustrated by JRR Tolkien - Regular & Deluxe Edition Hands-on Review
snippet.description:
Regular Edition US: https://amzn.to/3sQwLXz
Regular Edition UK: https://amzn.to/3RjrNwz
Deluxe Edition: tinyurl.com/4ewv2dcw

Product Description:
For the first time ever, a special enhanced edition of the enchanting prelude to The Lord of the Rings, illustrated throughout with over 50 sketches, drawings, paintings and maps by J.R.R. Tolkien himself and with the complete text printed in two colors.

Bilbo Baggins is a hobbit who enjoys a comfortable, unambitious life, rarely travelling further than the pantry of his hobbit-hole in Bag End. But his contentment is disturbed when the wizard, Gandalf, and a company of thirteen dwarves arrive on his doorstep one day to whisk him away on an unexpected journey ‘there and back again.’ They have a plot to raid the treasure hoard of Smaug the Magnificent, a large and very dangerous dragon . . .

Written for J.R.R. Tolkien’s own children, The Hobbit was published on 21 September 1937. With a beautiful cover design, a handful of black & white drawings and two maps by the author himself, the book became an instant success and was reprinted shortly afterwards with five color plates.

Tolkien’s own selection of finished paintings and drawings have become inseparable from his text, adorning editions of The Hobbit for more than 85 years. But the published art has afforded only a glimpse of Tolkien’s creative process, and many additional sketches, colored drawings and maps – although exhibited and published elsewhere – have never appeared within the pages of The Hobbit.

In this unique enhanced edition of Tolkien’s enchanting classic tale, the full panoply of his art is reproduced for the first time, presenting more than 50 illustrations to accompany Bilbo Baggins on his adventure ‘there and back again.’

00:00-09:35 Regular Edition
09:35-17:26 Deluxe Edition
17:26-19:47 What's Next?

#thehobbit #tolkien #review

snippet.title: THE BEST LORD OF THE RINGS EDITIONS | Book Collection
snippet.description:

snippet.title: This Deluxe Hobbit was ALMOST Great
snippet.description:
Publishers need to never do this again.

Craig dives into a review of the recent HarperCollins (via imprint William Morrow) edition of The Hobbit. It's part of a set of deluxe editions of Tolkien's major Middle-earth works, and follows the general footsteps of its predecessors, The Lord of the Rings and The Silmarillion. The question is, does including an extra item in the slipcase ruin this edition? Or enhance it?

0:00 - Prepping for my rant
0:45 - What they have in common
2:14 - Lower-tier edition review
6:51 - Deluxe edition review
8:19 - The rant
10:15 - Review continued
13:14 - Is it worth it?

snippet.title: Glaurung, Ancalagon, & the Dragons of The Silmarillion | Tolkien Explained
snippet.description:
Covering the origins and lives of the great dragons of the First Age.  Created by Morgoth to help defeat the Noldor, the dragons would be some of the most powerful and cunning of all evil beings.  Today, we feature the lives of Glaurung and Ancalagon the Black - the two most famous early dragons, as well as lesser known dragons like Gostir.

Glaurung, the father of dragons, shows his ability not only to destroy with his fire, but to manipulate with his words and bewitch with his gaze.  He even speaks with his master's voice at one point!  Ancalagon, the greatest and most powerful of Morgoth's dragons, would nearly win the War of Wrath for the Dark Lord, before being defeated in one of the most epic battles in Middle-earth History.

localized.title: Glaurung, Ancalagon, & the Dragons of The Silmarillion | Tolkien Explained
localized.description:
Covering the origins and lives of the great dragons of the First Age.  Created by Morgoth to help defeat the Noldor, the dragons would be some of the most powerful and cunning of all evil beings.  Today, we feature the lives of Glaurung and Ancalagon the Black - the two most famous early dragons, as well as lesser known dragons like Gostir.

Glaurung, the father of dragons, shows his ability not only to destroy with his fire, but to manipulate with his words and bewitch with his gaze.  He even speaks with his master's voice at one point!  Ancalagon, the greatest and most powerful of Morgoth's dragons, would nearly win the War of Wrath for the Dark Lord, before being defeated in one of the most epic battles in Middle-earth History.

*Hit subscribe - and the bell!*

snippet.title: The Balrogs of Morgoth | Tolkien Explained
snippet.description:
Today, we dive into the history of the Balrogs - from their origins as maiar, to becoming demons who served Morgoth, to their many deeds of the First Age.  We meet Gothmog, the Lord of Balrogs, who kills the elf kings Fëanor and Fingon, before meeting his own demise in Ecthelion.  We also cover Glorfindel's epic fight with a balrog, and how Durin's Bane reached Moria.  We also cover common balrog questions like: how many balrogs were there?  How many balrogs were left after the first age?  What did balrogs actually look like?  All this and more regarding your favorite demons of shadow and flame!

snippet.title: Obi-Wan Kenobi EPISODE 5 BREAKDOWN YES FINALLY!
snippet.description:
https://www.theorysabers.com
For me, this episode was a massive win. It portrayed Vader exactly how he should be, and how he is in the games and comics. It showed the beautiful training with Anakin and Obi-Wan and tied it into how each of them felt later on now in present day. It was magnificent. I really enjoyed this episode.

we start this episode off on coruscant, where anakin and obi wan are training together.

I loved how Kenobi tells them Vader is coming and he won’t stop for pleasantries or to be patient, when they ask how does he know, we get a flashback of Anakin and Obi-Wan’s fighting continued. This is amazing as it shows the lessons Obi-Wan was teaching Anakin which could have saved his life in their duel had he actually listened to them. Kenobi tells him that he grows too aggressive, a jedi’s goal is to defend life, not take it. This really shows some red flags with anakin and it does so perfectly. Portraying Anakin as the aggressor, which falls perfectly in line with his style of fighting, form 5 djem so, the offensive form. Whereas Obi-wan’s is soresu, form 3.

He realizes that the only way Reva can know that Vader is Anakin is if she was a youngling at the Jedi temple during order 66. He tells her Anakin killed younglings, and she has a flashback. She tells him that the younglings thought he was there to help them and that she hid with the bodies of her youngling friends. Kenobi realizes she isn’t serving Vader, but rather hunting him, to get closer to him. The rank of Grand Inquisitor grants the GI to be closer to Vader on dangerous missions, meaning more chances for Reva to fight or blind side Vader. Her anger with Kenobi is revealed as we learn she hates him to failing Anakin, and causing him to execute Order 66 on the Jedi. Blaming Obi-Wan for what happened to the galaxy and her friends.

Kenobi realizes he’s beaten, as we get another flashback of Anakin getting the upper hand on Obi-Wan. He strikes down on Obi-Wan who is cornered and defending himself down on a knee. This same angle mimics Luke attacking Vader in the same way in Return of the Jedi. the only difference is Anakin keeps attacking whereas Luke stops himself. Showing the difference between father and son. I also want to note that this choreography is very similar if not identical to their duel on Mustafar as they go through the tight walls into the control room. 

The flashback shows Anakin using his iconic behind the back move as he moves as swiftly as he did. Hayden doesn’t miss a beat after 17 years and continues to be a great swordsman with Ewan. He disarms obi-wan and learns a powerful lesson foreshadowing his loss on Mustafar.

As they ready to leave, Vader breaks through the doors and sees the ship taking off as he controls it with the force. This scene was the most badass scene I’ve seen with Disney’s Star Wars. This was straight out of force unleashed where starkiller was controlling the star destroyer, it echoed a lot of that scene. As he drops the ship down, he tears it apart with the powers of the dark side only to see the emergency shuttle escape and blast off into space, too fast for Vader to grab a hold of it.

The flashback concludes with Obi-Wan taking Anakin’s lightsaber with the force and telling him that he’s a great warrior, but his need to prove himself is his undoing. Until then, a padawan you will still be. As it shows Anakin’s immense disappointment in himself. As we get a shot from Anakin to Vader, showing exactly how he feels in this moment. 
As Reva tries to take him out from behind, he senses it and freezes her with the force, just like Fallen Order when he fought the second sister and Cal Kestis. He toys with her, completely making her look like a joke as he doesn’t even bother to use his lightsaber, as she’s not worthy of him using it. Vader just uses the force until he takes hers and splits it in two, throwing the other half to her feet. Besting her in lightsaber combat without even putting any effort into it. As she drops her to her knees he summons both sabers and for a moment I thought he was going to end her like how Anakin Skywalker did to Dooku, however he didn’t do that. He stood over her and plunged the saber into her, just as Anakin plunged it into her as a youngling. Now I watched this scene over and over again to confirm that he did indeed stab young Reva. We see her as a youngling make a face of pain as Anakin plunges it only to be connected to Vader finishing the movement. The first person POV of her keeling over dizzy as Anakin stands over her, is enough for me to believe the way this was shot and directed, is to imply that she was indeed stabbed as a youngling, just not fatally. Vader tells her that he knew all along that she was the youngling.

The rank of Grand Inquisitor grants the GI to be closer to Vader on dangerous missions, meaning more chances for Reva to fight or blind side Vader. Her anger with Kenobi is revealed as we learn she hates him to failing Anakin, and causing him to execute Order 66 on the Jedi. Blaming Obi-Wan for what happened to the galaxy and her friends.

Kenobi realizes he’s beaten, as we get another flashback of Anakin getting the upper hand on Obi-Wan. He strikes down on Obi-Wan who is cornered and defending himself down on a knee. This same angle mimics Luke attacking Vader in the same way in Return of the Jedi. the only difference is Anakin keeps attacking whereas Luke stops himself. Showing the difference between father and son. I also want to note that this choreography is very similar if not identical to their duel on Mustafar as they go through the tight walls into the control room. 

The flashback shows Anakin using his iconic behind the back move as he moves as swiftly as he did. Hayden doesn’t miss a beat after 17 years and continues to be a great swordsman with Ewan. He disarms obi-wan and learns a powerful lesson foreshadowing his loss on Mustafar.

As they ready to leave, Vader breaks through the doors and sees the ship taking off as he controls it with the force. This scene was the most badass scene I’ve seen with Disney’s Star Wars. This was straight out of force unleashed where starkiller was controlling the star destroyer, it echoed a lot of that scene. As he drops the ship down, he tears it apart with the powers of the dark side only to see the emergency shuttle escape and blast off into space, too fast for Vader to grab a hold of it.

The flashback concludes with Obi-Wan taking Anakin’s lightsaber with the force and telling him that he’s a great warrior, but his need to prove himself is his undoing. Until then, a padawan you will still be. As it shows Anakin’s immense disappointment in himself. As we get a shot from Anakin to Vader, showing exactly how he feels in this moment. 
As Reva tries to take him out from behind, he senses it and freezes her with the force, just like Fallen Order when he fought the second sister and Cal Kestis. He toys with her, completely making her look like a joke as he doesn’t even bother to use his lightsaber, as she’s not worthy of him using it. Vader just uses the force until he takes hers and splits it in two, throwing the other half to her feet. Besting her in lightsaber combat without even putting any effort into it. As she drops her to her knees he summons both sabers and for a moment I thought he was going to end her like how Anakin Skywalker did to Dooku, however he didn’t do that. He stood over her and plunged the saber into her, just as Anakin plunged it into her as a youngling. Now I watched this scene over and over again to confirm that he did indeed stab young Reva. We see her as a youngling make a face of pain as Anakin plunges it only to be connected to Vader finishing the movement. The first person POV of her keeling over dizzy as Anakin stands over her, is enough for me to believe the way this was shot and directed, is to imply that she was indeed stabbed as a youngling, just not fatally. Vader tells her that he knew all along that she was the youngling.

snippet.title: Obi-Wan Kenobi Episode 6 Breakdown THE END!!
snippet.description:
Obi-Wan tries to speak to Qui-Gon one last time as he observes his lightsaber. Saying it’s me or him and one of us needs to die. This is quite a line as Obi-Wan doesn’t normally live with such absolutes, but he knows that Vader wants to kill him and if he doesn’t succeed, then he’ll fail yoda, luke and everyone of the jedi who counted on him before. Obi-Wan heads to the planet nearby, as Vader falls for the bait, and orders the ship to follow Kenobi, as he takes his lambda t4a imperial shuttle down to meet Obi-Wan. The Grand Inquisitor disagrees with this move. 
Maybe Quinlan Voss arrives in season 2.

Reva arrives at the Lars homestead. 

Vader arrives on the planet, and he faces his former Master, obi-wan kenobi.

Have you come to destroy me, obi-wan? 
I will do what I must, says obi-wan, the same line he says to Anakin on Mustafar, as he gets into his Kenobi clone wars stance, the same stance he tried to fight maul in on tatooine a few years later, until he changed his stance to the qui-gon jinn one. 
So with this stance, it means Kenobi is pretty much as powerful as he was in revenge of the sith, like when he fought Grievous.
Then you will die, replies Vader, just like when he fought Ahsoka, as he charges kenobi, and we get them fighting with intense aggression and speed against one another. Keep in mind, this is Vader’s body, he’s immobile and this is really pushing his bad outdated cybernetics to the absolute limit as sidious gave him the literal worst mechanics in order to subdue him and punish him for losing to obi-wan kenobi on mustafar. In the old legends books, Vader was so immobile he couldn’t even raise his hands over his head, so all this is a stretch for him. In the brotherhood novel, it explains Anakin’s new robotic hand lags behind his organic one, so i can only imagine how Vader feels here. they get back to back like in their training flashback on coruscant. A lot of their fights are still mimicking their training as anakin and obi-wan in the good old days. It’s a nice connection.

Kenobi and Vader go at it, shredding rocks with their sabers, throwing boulders at each other with the force. As Kenobi drops a massive stone on Vader, who only shows him up in the force. It seems whatever vader lacks physically, he makes up for in the force. He performs a hulk smash with the force, breaking the floor as he gets the high ground on Kenobi, throwing boulder after boulder upon him, trapping Kenobi. 

Obi-Wan has a hard time as he’s collapsing under the pressure of the boulders, when he hears voices of anakin from their duel on mustafar, from their training on coruscant, and from Vader now, as he crumbles in defeat until he remembers Leia and his purpose in life now, to protect the children, to live for a new hope. He’s the last line of defence for them. This gives him enough power and belief in himself to fight for something important, as he sends the boulders sky high, and breaks out of there. Now i know people in th watch party had an issue with this part as he sneaks up on Vader, I think it’s because he’s using the force to stealthily move up to him, but of course Vader feels it. Jedi can suppress their footsteps and use the force to sneak around. Kenobi is using some of Anakin’s old moves, behind the hand twirl and spins, he’s using form 3 soresu, but he’s one the offence, which isn’t all that much like obi-wan, he’s much more of a defensive fighter, which is what form 3 soresu is.

We see Anakin, Hayden’s face, as Obi-Wan drops his guard and is brought to tears as he cries for Anakin.

Vader says, anakin is gone, i am what remains. This is all so sad. Obi-Wan tells him i’m sorry Anakin, for all of it. Now this is where i feel the directing was really well done, as we see the reflection of blue and red on anakin’s face, showing his inner conflict between the light and dark, between anakin skywalker and darth vader.
Vader tells him he is not his failure, that obi-wan didn’t kill anakin skywalker, he, himself, did. And I will destroy you, As he looks sadistic and psychotic. You can tell Vader is consumed by hatred, Anakin is still there, but he’s twisted and turned by the dark side.
Obi-Wan says in pity, then my friend is truly dead, as he walks away. He knows Vader is no longer a threat, and just feels sorry for him. There’s no need to kill someone he’s beaten now twice. It’s inconsistent with what kenobi tells luke to do later, to kill his father, but maybe Vader goes super psycho powerful over the next 10 years, who knows what the story of Vader will be going forwards. The scream Vader does for Obi-Wan tops the maul kenobi scream for me. It’s haunting and so full of rage and pain at being beaten and pitied.

snippet.title: OBI-WAN KENOBI EPISODE 3 BREAKDOWN VADER
snippet.description:
kenobi is once again reaching out to qui gon jinn, his old master. I guess in these 10 years he hasn’t been able to reach him. Yoda’s training hasn’t gone too well I guess.
as he hears voices of the past, like yoda telling him only pain will you find, qui gon’s plea to train anakin, reverberations of anakin on mustafaor, we see Vader being put together, really connecting the fact that anakin and vader are now the same person physically. obi wan can feel vader, and tells quigon that he is coming. 

As Vader walks out of his chamber, which looks lke the same one from Rogue One, we get a beautiful shot of mustafar and his castle. For those new to star wars, this is the same place where he fought obi-wan and lost, burning alive. This is also where in the comics, he opened a portal beneath his castle to bring back his dead wife padme, which of course didn’t work as planned. check out the marvel darth vader comics and darth momin for more about that.
Vader sits atop his obsidian throne, as he orders Reva around. Where is he, he says, and we hear this is james earl jones iconic voice. I feel it could be perfected with some audio engineering like how luke skywalker’s voice was made in the mandalorian, being completely computer generated.
He tells her that kenobi is all that matters, not the grand inquisitor. She clearly has lied and told Vader that Kenobi killed the GI, to which of course Vader will realize that this is impossible once he fights Kenobi and sees he’s pathetic.

He explains he knows what she wants, to be the grand inquisitor. If she brings him Kenobi, he will award her the promotion. If she fails, he’ll terminate her. So Vader has definitely given the go ahead to the Empire to track Kenobi down, and notify him once they have him in near sight. Vader ends communication and gets up like a robot, his lightsaber hanging from his belt, emitter side up, just like the original trilogy. 


As They land on Mapuzo, a mining system, we see a lifter droid and an R5 unit. R5 was the droid in a new hope that had the bad motivator, which was replaced by R2D2 to Luke Skywalker and Uncle Owen. This isn’t the same R5 unit, just a R5 unit.

As Obi-Wan looks out in to the distance, he sees dark side Anakin in his jedi robes. this is the first time we see Anakin played by hayden christensen in anything since revenge of the sith. I had to do a double take, I couldn’t believe it was him.

They enter a room that many Jedi have been in, this is a safe house, called the path. It all leads to Jabim, where they give the force sensitives captured by the empire, new identities and free them. As Leia asks what happens to them, it’s revealed no one ever sees them again. So I can say what happens to the is that the empire takes them in, and tries to convert them to the dark side. As Kenobi reveals carving on the walls from Quinlan Voss. This is amazing. We haven’t heard of Quinlan in forever, no one knew if he lived or died from Order 66. Quinlan was a powerful Jedi during the clone wars, he helped obi-wan on many missions and had a unique ability shared with Cal Kestis called psychometry.

I think this is Hayden in the suit. 

Kenobi runs away, and he’s stopped to see Vader infront of him. Igniting his crimson red lightsaber. Obi-Wan wants no part of this and runs away. Finally igniting his saber as Vader tells him he can’t hide forever.

We get the best line where Kenobi says what have you become? 
Vader puases and says I am what you made me.

They fight and it doesn’t look good for Kenobi at all, Vader overpowers him and he’s literally toying with him. 10 years have led to this moment, where Vader wants KEnobi to suffer. He’s also extremely cautious, as in this 10 years he’s had time to reflect on everything, and realizes his loss could have been avoided had he not been so arrogant and quick to make decisions. Rageful Vader is learning about Kenobi, he’s more tactful, more experienced, and more patient, waiting for the right time to unleash. 

Reva finds the safe house.

Vader lifts Kenobi with the dark side of the force, choking him, spilling flammable material, as Obi-Wan drops his lightsaber. 
Igniting the substance, Vader throws Obi-Wan into the fire, dragging him with the force, paying him back to how Obi-Wan left him on mustafar, burning alive. Telling him this is only the beginning for the pain he’s about to feel.
Vader clearly wants Obi-Wan to die very slowly, only after suffering to Vader’s enjoyment. That’s why he didn’t go all out, he’s savouring the moment. Playing with his food before he eats. As Storm troopers come, Vader orders them to bring him, when one is shot by the lady helping obi-wan, and she explodes a cannister into massive flames. Vader watches Kenobi being picked up by the loader droid who i think is wrecker or Rex, and we see the flames in his lenses. Symbolizing his rage and his past with obi-wan, the fires that turned him into who he is today.

snippet.title: Obi-Wan Kenobi Episode 4 Breakdown...
snippet.description:
kenobi wakes up in a hazy daze.
somehow Vader actually let Kenobi go and the fire stopped him. I hope this is addressed in the next 2 episodes because if it’s not, it won’t make any sense.
As he’s put in the bacta tank which accelerates his healing of burn wounds from Vader’s carnage, he seems to be connecting with Vader at the same moment in the bacta tank. If Vader is not on the field, he’s always in his bacta tank. His immense physical pain is something that is only somewhat subsided when he’s in his bacta. This is why his skin looks a bit more healed by the time return of the jedi rolls around, compared to now.
Vader and Kenobi seem to be sensing one another and it seems they each have their emotions linked or triggered by thoughts of the other. I think this would have been a great time to see Vader remember fighting Obi-Wan, maybe a new angle of him reaching out for Kenobi on Mustafar, just as Obi-Wan is seeing what Vader just did to him.
They get out of the bacta, and speak to Roken about where Leia is. Roken talks about how the inquisitors found his wife for being force sensitive or a jedi and took her. Roken figures out she’s at the inquisitor’s stronghold, where is in the middle of the ocean on the Nur moon in the Mustafar system. They recognize this is Vader’s system, which I guess is the first time Kenobi hears of it, and I would have liked to see a reaction from him about Mustafar. They decide to head over to the Inquitor’s HQ and save Leia. 
Reva interrogtaes Leia, telling her she knows of a safe house of Jedi in two star systems. She suspects Leia of knowing after telling her Obi-Wan died from Vader’s hand. I’m not sure why she’d suspect Leia of knowing anything, as she’s just the senator’s daughter.

game of thrones lady tries her imperial commanding officer uniform and gets into the computers to open the big door allowing Kenobi to enter in a similar fashion as we did in jedi fallen order.

Kenobi takes out some of the stormtroopers and moves in.
Reva mind probes Leia and it’s innefective. I loved this. I thought it was awesome that she resisted Reva without even trying or knowing the force. It just goes to show how powerful the Skywalker bloodline is, and how powerful luke and leia are even at this early age.

Reva talks again about how the Jedi took something from her. I am starting to believe she only wants to get up in the ranks of inquisitor because she wants to learn more about a lost brother she has. 

We get some Jedi Academy vibes as Kenobi uses the force to distract two troopers with a noise so he can get away.
 

As Kenobi makes his way through imperial restricted section he walks past Jedi from the prequels frozen in what looks like stasis. The first of which is Terra Sinube, the old jedi who helped Ahsoka find her lightsabers.

Some of the Jedi I can’t distinguish, one looks like it could be a longer haired Cere Junda, and the last is a Jedi Youngling, still with his training helmet on. So i think palpatine either has them as trophies or he’s going to use them for experiments on mount tantiss, or perhaps he already has and he’s just going to harvest their blood in the hopes that he has a suitable host for himself, for Grogu, or for Snoke.

The next scene is awesome as we get a reenactment of the Starkiller scene from force unleashed where he quickly takes out the stormtroopers in the darkness, and the only thing visible is his saber when it’s on. I loved the reference, and thought it’s great. As he runs out with Leia a seeker droid spots him, and sounds the alarm. Kenobi uses his lightsaber finally and redirects blaster bolts bak at his enemies. Even getting him doing his old Kenobi pose, which was nice to see. It seems he’s slowing remembering all his skills and techniques. We see a purge trooper from jedi fallen order, these are superior troopers with one goal only, to take out Jedi. They were like the inquisitor version of death troopers somewhat. 

Kenobi gets away to safety, and we see Vader angrily force choke the 3rd sister Reva as the other inquisitors watch on in terror. He is about to end her when she says she let them go. Vader releases her and she reveals she put a tracker on them. The tracker is Lola, Leia’s droid. He says he may have underestimated her which I thought was out of character as Vader seems to be constantly cutting her a lot of slack. 

He moves up to her and she confirms where he goes the tracker will follow. Vader is pleased.

We end the episode on Kenobi and the crew relaxing on the ship as it sails through space, with Lola’s light turning on, meaning the tacker is active.

If Vader is not on the field, he’s always in his bacta tank. His immense physical pain is something that is only somewhat subsided when he’s in his bacta. This is why his skin looks a bit more healed by the time return of the jedi rolls around, compared to now.
Vader and Kenobi seem to be sensing one another and it seems they each have their emotions linked or triggered by thoughts of the other. I think this would have been a great time to see Vader remember fighting Obi-Wan, maybe a new angle of him reaching out for Kenobi on Mustafar, just as Obi-Wan is seeing what Vader just did to him.
They get out of the bacta, and speak to Roken about where Leia is. Roken talks about how the inquisitors found his wife for being force sensitive or a jedi and took her. Roken figures out she’s at the inquisitor’s stronghold, where is in the middle of the ocean on the Nur moon in the Mustafar system. They recognize this is Vader’s system, which I guess is the first time Kenobi hears of it, and I would have liked to see a reaction from him about Mustafar. They decide to head over to the Inquitor’s HQ and save Leia. 
Reva interrogtaes Leia, telling her she knows of a safe house of Jedi in two star systems. She suspects Leia of knowing after telling her Obi-Wan died from Vader’s hand. I’m not sure why she’d suspect Leia of knowing anything, as she’s just the senator’s daughter.

game of thrones lady tries her imperial commanding officer uniform and gets into the computers to open the big door allowing Kenobi to enter in a similar fashion as we did in jedi fallen order.

Kenobi takes out some of the stormtroopers and moves in.
Reva mind probes Leia and it’s innefective. I loved this. I thought it was awesome that she resisted Reva without even trying or knowing the force. It just goes to show how powerful the Skywalker bloodline is, and how powerful luke and leia are even at this early age.

Reva talks again about how the Jedi took something from her. I am starting to believe she only wants to get up in the ranks of inquisitor because she wants to learn more about a lost brother she has. 

We get some Jedi Academy vibes as Kenobi uses the force to distract two troopers with a noise so he can get away.
 

As Kenobi makes his way through imperial restricted section he walks past Jedi from the prequels frozen in what looks like stasis. The first of which is Terra Sinube, the old jedi who helped Ahsoka find her lightsabers.

Some of the Jedi I can’t distinguish, one looks like it could be a longer haired Cere Junda, and the last is a Jedi Youngling, still with his training helmet on. So i think palpatine either has them as trophies or he’s going to use them for experiments on mount tantiss, or perhaps he already has and he’s just going to harvest their blood in the hopes that he has a suitable host for himself, for Grogu, or for Snoke.

The next scene is awesome as we get a reenactment of the Starkiller scene from force unleashed where he quickly takes out the stormtroopers in the darkness, and the only thing visible is his saber when it’s on. I loved the reference, and thought it’s great. As he runs out with Leia a seeker droid spots him, and sounds the alarm. Kenobi uses his lightsaber finally and redirects blaster bolts bak at his enemies. Even getting him doing his old Kenobi pose, which was nice to see. It seems he’s slowing remembering all his skills and techniques. We see a purge trooper from jedi fallen order, these are superior troopers with one goal only, to take out Jedi. They were like the inquisitor version of death troopers somewhat. 

Kenobi gets away to safety, and we see Vader angrily force choke the 3rd sister Reva as the other inquisitors watch on in terror. He is about to end her when she says she let them go. Vader releases her and she reveals she put a tracker on them. The tracker is Lola, Leia’s droid. He says he may have underestimated her which I thought was out of character as Vader seems to be constantly cutting her a lot of slack. 

He moves up to her and she confirms where he goes the tracker will follow. Vader is pleased.

We end the episode on Kenobi and the crew relaxing on the ship as it sails through space, with Lola’s light turning on, meaning the tacker is active.
